# Security & SecretsNever Hardcode Secrets

- No API keys, tokens, passwords, or credentials in code
- No AWS account IDs in Python code (pass via environment variables)
- No hardcoded ARNs (construct dynamically or pass via config)
Secrets Management
- Store secrets in AWS Secrets Manager — reference by name/ARN from environment variables
- Store runtime config/state in SSM Parameter Store
- Pass secret references to Lambdas via Terraform environment variables
# Correct: secret name from env var, value from Secrets Manager
secret_name = os.environ['WEBEX_CREDENTIALS']
secret = json.loads(secrets_client.get_secret_value(SecretId=secret_name)["SecretString"])
Files to Never Commit
- .env files
- *.tfvars files containing real credentials
- credentials.json, token.json, or similar
- Any file with plaintext secrets
Terraform Secrets
- Use sensitive = true on secret variables
- Pass secrets via CI/CD pipeline variables, not checked-in tfvars
- Never output secret values
Logging
- Never log full secret values, tokens, or credentials
- Mask or truncate sensitive data in log messages
- OK to log secret names/ARNs for debugging